{"id":"micha","term":"Micha","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(1.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 9:12\">2 Sam. 9:12</a> =MICAH (2).</p>\n<p>(2.) The son of Zabdi, a Levite of the family of Asaph (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 11:17\">Neh. 11:17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 11:22\">22</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["2 Samuel 9:12","Nehemiah 11:17","Nehemiah 11:22"]}